<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFCEFFE5FF6BFEC4FC51FD49" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCEFFE5FF6BFEC4FC1BFD89" blockId="20.[151,1127,290,793]" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FF6BFEC4FEB8FE89" bold="true" box="[151,262,290,313]" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Remarks.</emphasis>
The description of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FE27FEC4FD5FFE89" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[475,737,290,313]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semifasciata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FE27FEC4FD5FFE89" box="[475,737,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Coptocycla semifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
follows immediately that of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FBE0FEC4FE80FEE9" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jousselini">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FBE0FEC4FE80FEE9" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Coptocycla jousselini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCEFFE5FE89FEA4FD97FEE9" author="BOHEMAN" box="[373,553,322,345]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
differentiated them by elytral pattern. Both have the disc of pronotum and elytra brownish-red outside bordered by black and yellow explanate margins. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FF05FE64FE60FE29" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[249,478,386,409]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jousselini">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FF05FE64FE60FE29" box="[249,478,386,409]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Coptocycla jousselini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a yellow band running approximately in the basal third of elytra and reaching laterally the explanate margin, while in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FCEAFE44FC04FE09" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[790,954,418,441]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semifasciata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FCEAFE44FC04FE09" box="[790,954,418,441]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">C. semifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the first band is shortened and laterally reaching only to the fifth row of punctures. Both taxa were transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FF4FFE04FE9BFE49" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" box="[179,293,482,505]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FF4FFE04FE9BFE49" box="[179,293,482,505]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Charidotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCEFFE5FEB3FE04FE54FE49" author="SPAETH" box="[335,490,482,505]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCEFFE5FD6DFE04FC97FE49" author="SPAETH" box="[657,809,482,505]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref51203" refString="SPAETH F. 1926: Monographie der zu Gruppe der Coptocyclitae gehorigen amerikanischen Cassidinen (Col.): I. Die Gattungen mit gekammten Klauen. Supplementa Entomologica 13: 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1926">SPAETH (1926)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FC4EFE04FB86FE49" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[946,1080,482,505]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jousselini">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FC4EFE04FB86FE49" box="[946,1080,482,505]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">C. jousselini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and designated it as the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFCEFFE5FE9AFDE4FE2AFDA9" box="[358,404,514,537]" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FDF5FDE4FD05FDA9" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1926" box="[521,699,514,537]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microctenochira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FDF5FDE4FD05FDA9" box="[521,699,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Microctenochira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and after a decade he also transferred 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FBB2FDE4FEA2FD89" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semifasciata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FBB2FDE4FEA2FD89" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">C. semifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the same genus (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCEFFE5FE0DFDC4FDC4FD89" author="SPAETH" box="[497,634,546,569]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" pagination="66 - 99" refId="ref51359" refString="SPAETH F. 1936: Bestimmungstabelle der Gattung Charidotis (Col. Chrys. Cassid.). Sbornik Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze 14: 66 - 99." type="journal article" year="1936">SPAETH 1936</bibRefCitation>
), leaving it as valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCEFFE5FF49FDA4FC51FD49" blockId="20.[151,1127,290,793]" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">
I have studied 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFCEFFE5FEB6FDA4FE3CFDE9" box="[330,386,578,601]" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">types</typeStatus>
of both taxa and I could not find any relevant morphological differences to separate them except for the colouration of elytra. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FCA8FD84FBB8FDC9" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1926" box="[852,1030,610,633]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microctenochira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FCA8FD84FBB8FDC9" box="[852,1030,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Microctenochira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very variable regarding dorsal colouration. I hereby synonymize the two taxa. Since both were described in the same publication I followed the Principle of the first reviser (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCEFFE5FC1EFD44FBDDFD09" author="ICZN" box="[994,1123,674,697]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" refId="ref49784" refString="ICZN 1999: International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 24.2) and chose 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FE6DFD24FDA7FD69" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[401,537,706,729]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jousselini">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FE6DFD24FDA7FD69" box="[401,537,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">M. jousselini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid, as it was constantly and correctly applied since 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCEFFE5FF6BFD04FE91FD49" author="SPAETH" box="[151,303,738,761]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref51203" refString="SPAETH F. 1926: Monographie der zu Gruppe der Coptocyclitae gehorigen amerikanischen Cassidinen (Col.): I. Die Gattungen mit gekammten Klauen. Supplementa Entomologica 13: 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1926">SPAETH (1926)</bibRefCitation>
and moreover it is the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFCEFFE5FDD8FD04FDECFD49" box="[548,594,738,761]" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCEFFE5FCC9FD04FC59FD49" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1926" box="[821,999,738,761]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microctenochira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="295" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCEFFE5FCC9FD04FC59FD49" box="[821,999,738,761]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="295">Microctenochira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
